President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of South Carolina and authorized federal assistance to support recovery efforts from severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from February 6 to February 13, 2020. The federal funding will be available to state and eligible local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties of Anderson, Chester, Greenville, Newberry, Oconee, Pickens, and Spartanburg are specifically mentioned as areas eligible for funding. Additionally, federal funding will be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Allan Jarvis has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made if requested by the state and supported by damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.